This article is about a Presidential Memorandum issued on June 24, 2020. The memorandum pertains to a Presidential Determination pursuant to Section 303 of the Defense Production Act of 1950, as amended. The President determines that the industrial base production capability for ultra-high and high temperature composites for hypersonic, strategic missile, and space launch systems is essential to national defense. Without Presidential action, the United States industry cannot reasonably be expected to provide this production capability adequately and in a timely manner. The memorandum authorizes and directs the publication of this determination in the Federal Register.